snippet.textDisplay: Scar’s birth name is Taka, which roughly translates to “trash”, “garbage”, or “waste”. According to the book A Tale Of Two Brothers, he tricked a buffalo into attacking Mufasa when they were still cubs. After Mufasa escaped, the buffalo and his herd went after Scar instead, giving him his signature feature. The original movie’s director has said he was probably given a really mean nickname, but the book says he named himself Scar.
snippet.textOriginal: Scar’s birth name is Taka, which roughly translates to “trash”, “garbage”, or “waste”. According to the book A Tale Of Two Brothers, he tricked a buffalo into attacking Mufasa when they were still cubs. After Mufasa escaped, the buffalo and his herd went after Scar instead, giving him his signature feature. The original movie’s director has said he was probably given a really mean nickname, but the book says he named himself Scar.

snippet.textDisplay: This film wasn't a complete disaster, but it wasn't great. It did a lot wrong. Some REALLY flat line delivery. My biggest issue is what they decided to keep and what they decided to change. I definitely don't expect it to be verbatim. You have to change stuff for the new medium. In fact I was surprised how much WAS the same. But the stuff they did change was just SO misjudged. "Lions, attack?" Seriously? That line really REALLY pissed me off. In fact that whole scene did. They turned such an authentic and emotional scene into something dumbed down and cliche. And why did they extend Simba's return to Pride Rock and shoehorn Beyonce's song in there. Dumb.

If Walt Disney was alive now and still ran Disney I'm sure the live action remakes would not get made and we would have gotten a few more original animated movies.  Even if they are CGI.
